  "top_10_mapper_risk_gaps": [
    "AES has zero survey coverage anywhere — uniform prior or thermometer-circular inference",
    "morBoundaries 7-vector × intensity is highest-stakes derived inference; prototype on 2020 ANES first",
    "ONT_H requires Feldman-Stenner items only present in ANES — CES-only path effectively missing ONT_H",
    "COM essentially unmeasurable; mapper output near-uniform-prior across electorate",
    "CES Cumulative has zero issue-attitude vars; per-year merge required (~40-60 hrs per cycle)",
    "ANES year-specific codes not stable across cycles (V202xxx vs V162xxx vs V120xxx)",
    "MEANS-cluster (PRO+COM+AES) all weakly covered; vote prediction will be ENDS-driven",
    "TRB requires feeling-thermometer gaps absent from CES; CES-only TRB is crude proxy",
    "2024 ANES variable codes not directly verified this pass (PDF 403 to WebFetch)",
    "VCF item availability year-restricted; some items only post-1988 or post-1992; per-(node × year) availability matrix needed"
  ],
